ski]]<br />[[Patryk Dudek]]\n| {{FlagIOC2|AUS|2017 World Games}}<br />[[Jason Doyle]]<br />[[Chris Holder]]<br />[[Max Fricke]]\n| {{FlagIOC2|SWE|2017 World Games}}<br />[[Fredrik Lindgren (speedway rider)|Fredrik Lindgren]]<br />[[Antonio Lindb\u00e4ck]]<br />[[Peter Ljung (speedway rider)|Peter Ljung]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://worldgames2017.sportresult.com/nh/en/-120 Official website]\n* [https://worldgames2017.sportresult.com/nh/en/-120/Pdf/GetPdf?filename=resultbook%2F10th%20The%20World%20Games.pdf Complete results]\n* [http://www.theworldgames.org/ International World Games Association]\n\n{{World Games medal winners}}\n\n[[Category:2017 World Games|Medalists]]\n[[Category:Lists of World Games medalists|2017]]\n", "name_user": "Mohsen1248", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMuaythai", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_2017_World_Games_medal_winners"}
{"title_page": "Anna Harr", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n|name         = Anna Harr\n|image        = \n|image_size   =\n|caption      = \n|birthname    =\n|birth_date   = April 5, 2000\n|birth_place  = [[Phoenix, Arizona]], U.S.\n|occupation   = Actress\n|years_active = 2012\u2013present\n|iftaawards   =\n|awards       =\n}}\n\n'''Anna Harr''' is an American actress.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://occhimagazine.com/feature-actress-anna-harr-talks-about-her-starring-role-in-horror-film-of-krampus-origins/|title=Feature: Actress Anna Harr Talks About Her Starring Role in Horror Film of \"Krampus Origins\"|website=occhimagazine.com|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://us.blastingnews.com/showbiz-tv/2017/05/interview-with-actress-anna-harr-star-of-the-recent-horror-film-bethany-001716379.amp.html|title=Interview with actress Anna Harr, star of the recent horror film \u2018Bethany\u2019|website=us.blastingnews.com|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thehorrorcist.com/exclusive-interview-with-krampus-origins-anna-harr/|title=Exclusive Interview With Krampus Origins Anna Harr\n|website=thehorrorcist.com|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref> She is known for her work on the films ''Stasis'', ''Bethany'' and ''Krampus Origins''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scriptmag.com/features/sci-fi-circuit-stasis-underserved-low-budget-sci-fi-market|title=SCI-FI CIRCUIT: \u2018Stasis\u2019 and the Underserved Low-Budget Sci-Fi Market|website=scriptmag.com|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nerdalertnews.net/actress-anna-harr-chats-krampus-origins-and-latest-projects/|title=Actress Anna Harr chats \u2018Krampus Origins\u2019 and latest projects|website=nerdalertnews.net|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://themovieelite.com/interview-with-anna-harr-on-bethany/|title=Interview with Anna Harr on Bethany |website=themovieelite.com|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nAnna was born in [[Phoenix, Arizona]]. In 2017, she was cast in a role as Bethany/Young Claire in the film ''Bethany'' and played a lead role in the film ''Stasis'', later released by [[Netflix]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://spacejockeyreviews.com/bethany/|title=Bethany|website=spacejockeyreviews.com|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://martinatopic.com/2017/08/01/film-review-netflixs-stasis-2017/|title=#Film Review: Netflix\u2019s Stasis (2017)|website=martinatopic.com|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref> Her upcoming films ''Patsy Lee & The Keepers of the 5 Kingdoms'', ''Blood Craft'', ''Eminence Hill'', ''Rhea'' and more.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://horrorpedia.com/2019/03/07/blood-craft-movie-film-horror-2019-overview-cast-plot/|title=Blood Craft \u2013 USA, 2019|website=horrorpedia.com|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indieactivity.com/rhea-robert-conway-sci-fi-thriller-adds-anna-harr-caleb-thomas/|title=Rhea, Robert Conway\u2019s Sci-Fi thriller adds Anna Harr & Caleb Thomas|website=indieactivity.com|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Shake It Up (American TV series)|Shake It Up]]''\n| Shoe Rap Dancer\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[The Soup]]''\n| Child Director\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''A Lovely Afternoon''\n| Kerri\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''The Flip Side''\n| Party host\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Up North''\n| Mikey\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Ladykillers, Inc''\n| Kelly Smith\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Chasing the Sunset''\n| \n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Strange Blood]]''\n| Ella Moorehouse\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''The Woman of the Mountain''\n| Beth\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''A Beautiful Now''\n| Ballerina\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[The Curse of Sleeping Beauty]]''\n| Young Briar Rose\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''Restoration''\n| Katherine\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''Ghosthunters''\n| Gabby\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''Take a Stand''\n| Janie\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''Bethany''\n| Lynnie CoxBethany / Young Claire\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''Stasis''\n| Ava / Seattle\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Eleven Eleven''